        <briefdescription>
<para>Interface for applying deadzone handling to gamepad stick input.    </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Defines a method for processing and normalizing analog stick input while accounting for a deadzone. A deadzone eliminates unintended small input values caused by hardware imperfections. Implementations of this interface provide specific strategies for handling the deadzone and input normalization.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para>AxisDeadzoneStrategy for an axis-aligned deadzone implementation.    </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
